# GitHub Package Registry Configuration for @eln/lime
# 
# This file shows how to configure npm to install from GitHub.
# Copy this file to .npmrc and replace YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN with your actual token.
#
# To create a GitHub Personal Access Token:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Select scopes: repo (for private repos)
# 4. Copy the generated token

# For public repository (no authentication needed):
# Just run: npm install github:EarthLinkNetwork/lime

# For private repository:
# Uncomment the line below and replace YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN

# Alternative: Use SSH (recommended for development)
# npm install git+ssh://git@github.com:EarthLinkNetwork/lime.git

# For CI/CD environments, use environment variable:
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}
